ClaimItems

ClaimItemsUpdate

update a claim item

Authorizations:
oauth2
path Parameters
id
required
string

claim item ID

Request Body schema: application/json

claim item update input object

fmv
integer <int64> (Currency)

Currency is in US Dollars, specified as an integer representing cents ($0.01 USD is represented as 1 and $105.36 as 10536)

is_repairable
boolean

is item repairable?

payout_option
string (PayoutOption)

may be one of: Repair, Replacement, FMV, FixedFraction

repair_actual
integer <int64> (Currency)

Currency is in US Dollars, specified as an integer representing cents ($0.01 USD is represented as 1 and $105.36 as 10536)

repair_estimate
integer <int64> (Currency)

Currency is in US Dollars, specified as an integer representing cents ($0.01 USD is represented as 1 and $105.36 as 10536)

replace_actual
integer <int64> (Currency)

Currency is in US Dollars, specified as an integer representing cents ($0.01 USD is represented as 1 and $105.36 as 10536)

replace_estimate
integer <int64> (Currency)

Currency is in US Dollars, specified as an integer representing cents ($0.01 USD is represented as 1 and $105.36 as 10536)

Responses

https://localhost/claim-items/{id}

Request samples

  • Payload
Content type
application/json
{
  • "fmv": 0,
  • "is_repairable": true,
  • "payout_option": "string",

  • "repair_estimate": 0,
  • "replace_actual": 0,
  • "replace_estimate": 0
}

Claims

ClaimsList

List the claims visible to the authenticated user, filtered by the given status values. For a user, all status values are included by default. For an admin (steward or signator) only the review status values are included by default. Accepted status values: Draft, Review1, Review2, Review3, Revision, Receipt, Approved, Paid, Denied

Authorizations:
oauth2
query Parameters
status
string

comma-separated list of status values to include

Responses

https://localhost/claims

ClaimsDeny

Admin denies a claim. Can be used at states "Review1","Review2","Review3".

Authorizations:
oauth2
path Parameters
id
required
string

claim ID

Request Body schema: application/json

claim deny input object

status_reason
string

message from a reviewer noting the reason for the new status, e.g. detailing the revisions needed

Responses

https://localhost/claims/{id}/deny

boolean

is item repairable?

string <uuid4>

item ID

payout_option
string (PayoutOption)

integer <int64> (Currency)

integer <int64> (Currency)

Currency is in US Dollars, specified as an integer representing cents ($0.01 USD is represented as 1 and $105.36 as 10536)

replace_actual
integer <int64> (Currency)

Currency is in US Dollars, specified as an integer representing cents ($0.01 USD is represented as 1 and $105.36 as 10536)

replace_estimate
integer <int64> (Currency)

Currency is in US Dollars, specified as an integer representing cents ($0.01 USD is represented as 1 and $105.36 as 10536)

LedgerReportCreate

Create and return a report on the ledger entries as specified by the input object. The returned object contains metadata and a File object pointing to a CSV file suitable for use with Sage Accounting.

Report types:

  • monthly - Return all ledger entries not yet reconciled, up to the beginning of the given day (0:00 UTC).
  • annual - Return the billing detail for given year's policy renewals.
Authorizations:
oauth2
Request Body schema: application/json

LedgerReportCreateInput object

date
string

Report date, e.g. return the ledger entries prior to the given date. Details vary by the report type.

type
string

Report types:

  • monthly - Return all ledger entries not yet reconciled, up to the beginning of the given date.
  • annual - Return the policy renewal entries for the year of the given date.

PolicyLedgerReportCreate

Create and return a report on the ledger entries of a policy as specified by the input object. The returned object contains metadata and a File object pointing to a CSV file. If no ledger entries are found with a date_entered value that matches the requested Type, Year and (if applicable) Month, then a 204 is returned.

Authorizations:
oauth2
path Parameters
id
required
string

policy ID

Request Body schema: application/json

PolicyLedgerReportCreateInput object

month
integer <int64>

Report month, e.g. return the policy's ledger entries entered in that month and year. The month and year (together) must not be in the future. For annual reports only, the month may be 0.

type
string

Report types:

  • Monthly - Return all ledger entries not yet reconciled, up to the beginning of the given date.
  • Annual - Return the policy renewal entries for the year of the given date.
year
integer <int64>

Report year, e.g. return the policy's ledger entries entered in that year.

Responses

https://localhost/policies/{id}/ledger-reports
